{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[PASS 1 / T8 — LLM/prompt structural-completeness probe] N/A (overlay does not apply): this plan defines a state-machine reducer (`managed_refs` provenance fold in `compiled_state`) and a pure, provider-agnostic decision gate (`should_propagate_removal`), with no LLM/agent surface — no prompts, sub-agents, reviewers, LLM output schemas, or model-consumed enums. The only enum-like vocabulary, the ref-kind set `{parent, blocks, depends_on, relates_to}`, is a fully-defined data-domain key (normalized `(kind, target_local_id)`), not an LLM output schema, so the \"undefined-but-referenced enum\" probe is satisfied inline. The gate's decision rule (peer-present + locally-absent ⇒ REMOVE iff ∈ managed_refs, else ADOPT) is co-located with the set it consumes, and the failed/incomplete-sub-step fallback is explicitly specified (missing/absent managed_refs ⇒ empty ⇒ gate returns False, additive-only safe no-op). No counter-placement ambiguity, no pink-elephant/instruction-locality antipattern. T8 CLEAN (empty findings)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782538350886058001,"uuid":"0367d784-d68d-4493-a0b6-c05a60970800"}